        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implement connection pooling and set timeouts to 30 seconds for synchronous calls. For asynchronous workflows, use webhook callbacks to handle responses."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimizing Performance and Reducing Latency"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To minimize latency, enable HTTP/2 and compress payloads with gzip. Batch multiple inference requests where possible, but keep batch sizes under 50 to avoid timeouts. Monitor p99 latency and adjust thread pools based on CPU utilization. Use caching for repeated queries with identical parameters."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementing Robust Error Handling and Retries"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Design idempotent retry mechanisms for transient errors (e.g., HTTP 429 or 503). Exponential backoff with a base delay of 100ms is recommended. Log all errors with correlation IDs for tracing. Validate input schemas client-side to reduce invalid requests."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Monitoring, Logging, and Scaling Strategies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Instrument your API calls with metrics for request volume, error rates, and latency histograms. Use tools like OpenTelemetry for distributed tracing. Scale horizontally by deploying multiple API instances behind a load balancer, and auto-scale based on CPU or queue depth thresholds."
